\fs36 \cf0 Dragon
\fs22 \
The Dragons of Etan start out as vicious flightless lizards about half the size of a horse, but they grow into sky dwelling terrors.  As with Wolfens, having a Dragon in your party means few innkeepers will let you stay in their rooms, but the advantages often out-weigh the trouble of camping outside.  There are two types of Dragons available to join your party, Firebrand and Sylavin.  The differences between them become more apparent as they progress through the ranks, and gain magical abilities.  One of your adventurers must be a Beastmaster to have a Dragon in your party.
